{
    "id": 23271,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - June 16, 2014",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 253.536,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 253.536,
                "byte_start": 107520,
                "byte_stop": 1121593,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 7.644,
                        "byte_start": 107520,
                        "byte_stop": 138136,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.644,
                                "byte_start": 107520,
                                "byte_stop": 138136,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has our opinion this morning in case 12-1493 Abramski v. United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.644,
                        "stop": 253.536,
                        "byte_start": 138136,
                        "byte_stop": 1121593,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.644,
                                "stop": 13.546,
                                "byte_start": 138136,
                                "byte_stop": 161750,
                                "text": "Federal law tightly regulates the sale of guns by licensed firearms dealers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.546,
                                "stop": 28.253,
                                "byte_start": 161750,
                                "byte_stop": 220578,
                                "text": "An issue in this case is a provision of the Federal Criminal Code Section 922(a)(6) which makes a criminal for a would-be gun buyer to lie to the dealer about any fact material to the lawfulness of the sale."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.253,
                                "stop": 34.129,
                                "byte_start": 220578,
                                "byte_stop": 244088,
                                "text": "We had to decide in this case whether that provision applies to a straw purchase of a gun."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.129,
                                "stop": 41.719,
                                "byte_start": 244088,
                                "byte_stop": 274495,
                                "text": "That is when a person buys a gun on behalf of someone else while falsely claiming that it is for himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.719,
                                "stop": 49.166,
                                "byte_start": 274495,
                                "byte_stop": 304274,
                                "text": "In this case, petitioner, Bruce Abramski, offered to buy a gun for his uncle believing that he could get a discount on the purchase."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.166,
                                "stop": 52.429,
                                "byte_start": 304274,
                                "byte_stop": 317336,
                                "text": "His uncle agreed and sent Abramski a check."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.429,
                                "stop": 56.32,
                                "byte_start": 317336,
                                "byte_stop": 332904,
                                "text": "Abramski then went to a licensed gun dealer to buy the gun."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.32,
                                "stop": 65.162,
                                "byte_start": 332904,
                                "byte_stop": 368222,
                                "text": "There, he had to fill out a federal form that asked him whether he was the actual transferee\/buyer of the firearm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.162,
                                "stop": 74.767,
                                "byte_start": 368222,
                                "byte_stop": 406674,
                                "text": "In conspicuous bold letters, the form warned him that he was not the actual buyer if he was purchasing the gun on behalf of some other person."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.767,
                                "stop": 80.315,
                                "byte_start": 406674,
                                "byte_stop": 428826,
                                "text": "Nonetheless, Abramski answered yes, that he was the actual buyer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.315,
                                "stop": 86.902,
                                "byte_start": 428826,
                                "byte_stop": 455158,
                                "text": "After leaving the store with the gun, he cashed the check his uncle had given him and then gave the gun to his uncle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.902,
                                "stop": 93.082,
                                "byte_start": 455158,
                                "byte_stop": 479922,
                                "text": "The Government indicted Abramski under Section 922(a)(6) for making the false statement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.082,
                                "stop": 100.296,
                                "byte_start": 479922,
                                "byte_stop": 508761,
                                "text": "Abramski moved to dismiss the indictment claiming that his full statement was not material to the lawfulness of the sale."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.296,
                                "stop": 102.291,
                                "byte_start": 508761,
                                "byte_stop": 516702,
                                "text": "The District Court rejected that argument."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.291,
                                "stop": 108.2,
                                "byte_start": 516702,
                                "byte_stop": 540421,
                                "text": "Abramski pled guilty and then appealed the District Court\u0027s decision but the Fourth Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.2,
                                "stop": 112.062,
                                "byte_start": 540421,
                                "byte_stop": 555781,
                                "text": "And today, we also affirm the Fourth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.062,
                                "stop": 121.489,
                                "byte_start": 555781,
                                "byte_stop": 593502,
                                "text": "Abramski\u0027s primary argument is that Section 922(a)(6) simply doesn\u0027t apply to misstatements in connection with straw purchasers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.489,
                                "stop": 129.362,
                                "byte_start": 593502,
                                "byte_stop": 625058,
                                "text": "In his view, the federal gun law is concerned only with the identity of the person who shows up at the dealer\u0027s counter to obtain the gun."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.362,
                                "stop": 138.796,
                                "byte_start": 625058,
                                "byte_stop": 662779,
                                "text": "On that view, the sale to him would have been lawful even if he had admitted that he was a straw purchaser, so his misrepresentation was not material."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.796,
                                "stop": 140.576,
                                "byte_start": 662779,
                                "byte_stop": 669884,
                                "text": "We think that\u0027s wrong."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.576,
                                "stop": 145.347,
                                "byte_start": 669884,
                                "byte_stop": 689006,
                                "text": "The text of the gun law alone leaves some ambiguity on this question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.347,
                                "stop": 148.679,
                                "byte_start": 689006,
                                "byte_stop": 702276,
                                "text": "It refers merely to persons and transferees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.679,
                                "stop": 160.609,
                                "byte_start": 702276,
                                "byte_stop": 750028,
                                "text": "It doesn\u0027t say whether in a case like this one, that means the man at the counter or the man who was a result of the transaction will actually come away with ownership and control of the gun."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.609,
                                "stop": 167.467,
                                "byte_start": 750028,
                                "byte_stop": 777404,
                                "text": "But we think that when the languages read in its broader context, it clearly refers to the true buyer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.467,
                                "stop": 178.96,
                                "byte_start": 777404,
                                "byte_stop": 823380,
                                "text": "The focus on the straw who may possess the gun for all of the minute rather than the always intended true buyer would virtually repeal core provisions of the federal gun law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 178.96,
                                "stop": 186.851,
                                "byte_start": 823380,
                                "byte_stop": 854936,
                                "text": "Under federal law, a dealer may not sell to anyone legally prohibited from owning a firearm like felons and the mentally ill."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.851,
                                "stop": 198.331,
                                "byte_start": 854936,
                                "byte_stop": 900911,
                                "text": "To enforce that prohibition, the law requires that the buyer show up in person, provide his name, age and address, show a photo I.D. and pass a federal background check."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.331,
                                "stop": 209.421,
                                "byte_start": 900911,
                                "byte_stop": 945215,
                                "text": "The law also imposes record-keeping requirements to enforce those provisions and to assist law enforcement officers in investigating crimes by tracing guns to buyers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 209.421,
                                "stop": 211.973,
                                "byte_start": 945215,
                                "byte_stop": 955455,
                                "text": "Those provisions would all mean very little."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.973,
                                "stop": 222.723,
                                "byte_start": 955455,
                                "byte_stop": 998504,
                                "text": "If a would-be gun buyer could evade them all, merely by enlisting an intermediary and having him fill out the paperwork and undergo the requisite background check."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.723,
                                "stop": 231.365,
                                "byte_start": 998504,
                                "byte_stop": 1032986,
                                "text": "In this case, we follow our usual practice of ignoring shams when identifying the real parties to a transaction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.365,
                                "stop": 245.265,
                                "byte_start": 1032986,
                                "byte_stop": 1088679,
                                "text": "The opinion also addresses and rejects a couple of alternative arguments Mr. Abramski makes under -- makes under Section 922(a)(6) as well as under another full statement provision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 245.265,
                                "stop": 253.536,
                                "byte_start": 1088679,
                                "byte_stop": 1121593,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice, Justice Thomas and Justice Alito joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
